--interface wlo1 (Defaulted, non-required unless wanted)
--ssid Defaults to drone-swarm-net
--setup-net Do not run on either machine during live on different computers. Required on one instance if run locally (Sets one instance to handle the connection)
--drone-id set name of the drone

sudo python3 f.py --drone-id drone_1 --interface wlo1 --ssid drone-swarm-net --setup-net --tcp-port 20000 --udp-port 20001

----------------
Manually set up ad-hoc network



------------------------------
Verification if drones are on the same network:
# Make sure you really are in IBSS on the same channel/SSID
iw dev wlo1 link
# Expect: "Connected to ... (on IBSS)" + SSID drone-swarm-net + freq 2437 (ch 6)

# See if you can see the other peer's beacons (optional)
iw dev wlo1 scan | grep -A3 -i 'drone-swarm-net'

# Watch for discovery traffic
sudo tcpdump -ni wlo1 udp port 19999

# Temporarily open the firewall (or allow the specific port)
sudo ufw status
sudo ufw allow 19999/udp

